heaviest_rainfall.status: The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm fell at a maximum rate of 4.6mm per hour over the 37.2 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: On 02 September 2025, the rain fell at an exceptional rate, peaking at 27.0mm per hour, the heaviest downpour recorded.  A total of 21.19mm fell over the 15.0 hour storm.

longest_rain.status: A storm today ranked 5th for the longest continuous rainfall according to our records, lasting a total of22.9 hours.  It came with 7.68mm of rainfall, at times, falling at {this_max}mm per hour.  Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.

summary.description:
Today, cooler for the feels like temperature (down 6.4°C) and outside temperature (down 4.5°C) and drier conditions in outside humidity (down 9%) and rainfall (down 0.2 mm).

Compared to today, yesterday also had noticeable differences in rainfall (up 0.2 mm) and pressure (up 5 mbar).

The past week and month had observable variation in rainfall (down 0.3 mm), cloud levels (up 380 m), and light levels (up 2870 lux) when compared to today.
